1. Switches allow us to connect loads of devices within a LAN and uses the devices MAC
   address to send data to different destinations.
   Switches helps solve security issues and also help with organizing.

2. When data is sent to a switch it gets sent with a header that contains the MAC address of the
   destination. The switch then uses the MAC address to send the data to the correct destination.
   MAC addresses are addresses assigned to physical devices like printers and computers.


